               Transported for Seven years
            </rs>.</p>
               <p>MR. GRAY here stated that he had since made a calculation, and allowing very linerally for the consumption of corn by the horses, there was a deficiency of forty-five quarters unaccounted for, in the space of six weeks.</p>
